BlackRock CEO Larry Fink <a href="https://twitter.com/EleanorTerrett/status/1714004148826374403?t=LstMOZHBH1yhcBCYg0mwyQ&amp;s=19" data-v-f87c67ca="">said Monday</a> that a rally in the price of bitcoin triggered by a false news report about the approval of a spot ETF served as an example of the "pent up interest in crypto."<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
Fink, who said that he couldn't comment on the specifics of his own firm's pending application for a spot bitcoin ETF, said he'd been hearing "from clients from around the world about the need for crypto."&nbsp;
